        <h2>What Data We Store</h2>
        <p>When you sign in with Facebook, we collect and store:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> Your Facebook user ID, name, and email address</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Picture:</strong> Your Facebook profile picture URL (if available)</li>
            <li><strong>Authentication Token:</strong> OAuth access token (expires automatically)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Delete Your Data</h2>
        <p>You have <strong>two options</strong> to delete your Facebook data from CSFrace:</p>

        <h3>Option 1: Delete Your CSFrace Account</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Log in to your CSFrace account at <a href="https://localhost:3000" target="_blank">https://localhost:3000</a></li>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Account</strong></li>
            <li>Click on <strong>"Delete Account"</strong></li>
            <li>Confirm the deletion</li>
        </ol>
        <p>This will permanently delete all your data from our system, including your Facebook information.</p>

        <h3>Option 2: Disconnect Your Facebook Account</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Log in to your CSFrace account at <a href="https://localhost:3000" target="_blank">https://localhost:3000</a></li>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Connected Accounts</strong></li>
            <li>Find <strong>Facebook</strong> in the list of connected accounts</li>
            <li>Click <strong>"Disconnect"</strong> next to Facebook</li>
        </ol>
        <p>This will remove your Facebook connection and delete all Facebook-related data while keeping your CSFrace account active (if you have other login methods).</p>

        <h3>Option 3: Request Manual Deletion</h3>
        <p>If you're unable to access your account, you can request manual data deletion:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Send an email to: <a href="mailto:privacy@csfrace.com">privacy@csfrace.com</a></li>
            <li>Include your Facebook email address or user ID</li>
            <li>Subject line: "Facebook Data Deletion Request"</li>
            <li>We will process your request within <strong>30 days</strong></li>
        </ol>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</strong> Data deletion is <strong>permanent and cannot be undone</strong>. Make sure you want to delete your data before proceeding.
        </div>

        <h2>What Happens After Deletion</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Your Facebook profile information is immediately removed from our database</li>
            <li>Your profile picture URL is deleted</li>
            <li>OAuth tokens are revoked and removed</li>
            <li>You will no longer be able to sign in with Facebook (unless you reconnect)</li>
            <li>Deletion is processed within <strong>24-48 hours</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We do <strong>NOT</strong> retain your Facebook data after deletion, except:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> If required by law to retain certain data</li>
            <li><strong>Backup Systems:</strong> Backups are purged on a rolling 30-day cycle</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-Party Data</h2>
        <p>This deletion request only removes your data from <strong>CSFrace</strong>. To manage your Facebook data:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to <a href="https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=applications" target="_blank">Facebook Settings ‚Üí Apps and Websites</a></li>
            <li>Find <strong>CSFrace</strong> in the list</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Remove</strong> to revoke CSFrace's access to your Facebook data</li>
        </ol>

